007import edu.wpi.first.hal.AllianceStationID;

012/** Class to control a simulated driver station. */
013public final class DriverStationSim {
014  private DriverStationSim() {
015    throw new UnsupportedOperationException("This is a utility class!");
016  }
017
018  /**
019   * Register a callback on whether the DS is enabled.
020   *
021   * @param callback the callback that will be called whenever the enabled state is changed
022   * @param initialNotify if true, the callback will be run on the initial value
023   * @return the {@link CallbackStore} object associated with this callback. Save a reference to
024   *     this object so GC doesn't cancel the callback.
025   */
026  public static CallbackStore registerEnabledCallback(
027      NotifyCallback callback, boolean initialNotify) {
028    int uid = DriverStationDataJNI.registerEnabledCallback(callback, initialNotify);
029    return new CallbackStore(uid, DriverStationDataJNI::cancelEnabledCallback);
030  }
031

033   * Check if the DS is enabled.
034   *
035   * @return true if enabled
036   */
037  public static boolean getEnabled() {
038    return DriverStationDataJNI.getEnabled();
039  }

048  }

223  /**
224   * Get the alliance station ID (color + number).
225   *
226   * @return the alliance station color and number
227   */
228  public static AllianceStationID getAllianceStationId() {
229    switch (DriverStationDataJNI.getAllianceStationId()) {
230      case 0:
231        return AllianceStationID.Red1;
232      case 1:
233        return AllianceStationID.Red2;
234      case 2:
235        return AllianceStationID.Red3;
236      case 3:
237        return AllianceStationID.Blue1;
238      case 4:
239        return AllianceStationID.Blue2;
240      case 5:
241        return AllianceStationID.Blue3;
242      default:
243        return null;
244    }
245  }
246
247  /**
248   * Change the alliance station.
249   *
250   * @param allianceStationId the new alliance station
251   */
252  public static void setAllianceStationId(AllianceStationID allianceStationId) {
253    int allianceStation;
254    switch (allianceStationId) {
255      case Red1:
256        allianceStation = 0;
257        break;
258      case Red2:
259        allianceStation = 1;
260        break;
261      case Red3:
262        allianceStation = 2;
263        break;
264      case Blue1:
265        allianceStation = 3;
266        break;
267      case Blue2:
268        allianceStation = 4;
269        break;
270      case Blue3:
271        allianceStation = 5;
272        break;
273      default:
274        return;
275    }
276    DriverStationDataJNI.setAllianceStationId(allianceStation);
277  }

311  /** Updates DriverStation data so that new values are visible to the user program. */

314    DriverStation.waitForData();

488  /**
489   * Sets the match type.
490   *
491   * @param type the match type
492   */
493  public static void setMatchType(DriverStation.MatchType type) {
494    int matchType;
495    switch (type) {
496      case Practice:
497        matchType = 1;
498        break;
499      case Qualification:
500        matchType = 2;
501        break;
502      case Elimination:
503        matchType = 3;
504        break;
505      case None:
506        matchType = 0;
507        break;
508      default:
509        return;
510    }
511    DriverStationDataJNI.setMatchType(matchType);
512  }
